By the lex Cornelia of Sulla, exile was cer- tainly established as a punishment (Cic. Verr. ii 31)Í¾ quad- ruple reimbursement was introduced, and probably a mild sorm os infamia. The question unfortunately came to be mixed up with the party struggle between the optimates and populares, and equestrian iudices were substituted sor senatorial, and senatorial for equestrian, with very little advantage to the provincials. But still a certain advance was made, though much yet remained to be improved. The provincial governors were still masters through the iudicia of the property ol the provincials. They could exact illegal taxes, and enforce ,con- tributions in the form os money, corn, or ships, while their opportunities of private plunder were innumerable.
